# OL-CNT-004 Pickaxe Catalog

## Purpose

The Pickaxe Catalog defines all usable Pickaxes in OreLabs.

Pickaxes are progression tools that determine how quickly the player can mine Ores.

The catalog exists to organize all Pickaxes in a single structured system.

---

## Core Philosophy

Pickaxes are bought through progression.

They are tied to Strength requirements and usually cost Coins as well.

A new Pickaxe should always feel like a meaningful upgrade.

Pickaxes are not just equipment.

They are milestones in the player's progression.

---

## Player Experience

The player should feel:

- I finally have enough Strength for a better Pickaxe.
- I can buy this Pickaxe now.
- My new Pickaxe feels stronger.
- I want to compare it with older Pickaxes.
- I want to keep progressing.

A Pickaxe purchase should always feel rewarding.

---

## Shop Structure

Pickaxe purchase happens in a central shop structure.

The shop may also contain other progression items such as:

- Backpacks
- Future upgrades
- Future systems

When the player buys a Pickaxe, it equips immediately.

The player may later re-equip older Pickaxes from the shop interface.

Pickaxes are not required to remain in a separate inventory system.

---

## Unlock Rules

Pickaxes are primarily unlocked through Strength.

Some Pickaxes may also require:

- Coins
- Rebirth milestones
- Quests
- Special Events
- Secret Discovery
- Future systems

Strength is the main gate to progression.

---

## Equip Rules

Buying a Pickaxe equips it immediately.

The player may manually equip any previously unlocked Pickaxe through the shop.

This keeps progression simple and easy to understand.

---

## Pickaxe Progression

Each Pickaxe represents a new stage of mining power.

Pickaxes should feel stronger through:

- higher Mining Damage
- better efficiency
- faster mining
- smoother progression

Pickaxes do not require special hidden ore-specific modifiers.

Their effectiveness is determined by their damage and the Ore's Health.

---

## Forge Relationship

The Forge does not improve existing Pickaxes.

Instead, the Forge creates its own custom Pickaxes.

Forge-crafted Pickaxes may later become part of a separate advanced catalog.

This keeps the standard Pickaxe progression and Forge progression distinct.

---

## Special Pickaxes

Not all Pickaxes must come from the shop.

Some Pickaxes may be obtained through:

- Quests
- Events
- Secrets
- Future systems
- Forge crafting

These Pickaxes should feel special and memorable.

---

## Relationship with Other Systems

Depends on:

- Strength System

Supports:

- Mining System
- Ore System
- Economy
- Rebirth
- Forge
- Future Systems

---

## Design Rules

- Every Pickaxe must feel like progress.
- Pickaxes should be easy to understand.
- Stronger Pickaxes should never break the core mining system.
- The shop should allow the player to inspect and re-equip unlocked Pickaxes.
- Forge-crafted Pickaxes must remain separate from normal shop progression.

---

## Future Extensions

Possible future additions:

- Pickaxe Skins
- Pickaxe Traits
- Legendary Pickaxes
- Secret Pickaxes
- Event Pickaxes
- Forge-only Pickaxes

---

## Success Criteria

The Pickaxe Catalog is successful when:

- players are excited to unlock the next Pickaxe;
- the shop feels useful and clean;
- older Pickaxes remain accessible;
- special Pickaxes feel memorable;
- the system stays simple and scalable.

---

## Pickaxe Principle

> A Pickaxe is a progression milestone first, and a tool second.
>
> Buying a Pickaxe should always feel like unlocking the next stage of the game.
